    <body>
        <p>Cursor movement is controlled using position keyframes. Each position keyframe represents the cursor's position on the frame at a specific time. If you automatically added cursors to your movie, position keyframes will be added to the timeline for you.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Click on an cursor that contains one or more position keyframes.</p>
                <p>A trajectory (blue dotted path) appears near the object.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../Images/cursor1.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth80Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
            <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="MimicGuides.MimicMovieEnhancementGuide" />
            <li>Click on a point (larger blue circle) within the trajectory. The point you selected turns yellow.</li>
            <li>
                <p>Drag the point to a new place in the Frame Editor.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../Images/cursor2.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth80Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>You can also add additional position keyframes if you want the cursor to move along a more specific path. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Objects/Keyframes/Adding_Keyframes.htm">Adding Keyframes</MadCap:xref>.</p>
    </body>
</html>